  "body": "- [x] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nThe compilation would fetch all versions from the Internet every time I compiled something. \r\ncase 1: I have version = \"native\"\r\ncase 2: I have version = \"0.4.25\"\r\n\r\nNeither would prevent the process from fetching the sole version info. \r\n\r\nEffectively I could not use truffle without the Internet.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nHere is what I have in the truffle-config.js:\r\n  compilers: {\r\n        solc: {\r\n            // version: \"native\",   // let's use the native for faster work. bran: slower for small project!!\r\n            settings: {\r\n                optimizer: {\r\n                    enabled: true, // Default: false\r\n                    // runs: 100     // Default: 200\r\n                },\r\n                //evmVersion: \"homestead\"  // Default: \"byzantium\"\r\n            },\r\n            version: \"0.4.25\"\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System:  OSX\r\n* Ethereum client: built-in or Ganache\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): Truffle v5.0.0-beta.1\r\n* node version (`node --version`): v10.10.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 6.4.1\r\n\r\n",
